05/04/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova said Sunday (4 April) that extremists and outsiders in Kosovo spurred two days of deadly ethnic violence last month, the most serious episode since the UN came to the province. 
In an interview with the <I>Sunday Telegraph</I>, Rugova called on the United Kingdom to keep its troops in the province and help achieve independence. 
(B92 - 04/04/04)
